---
// Voxel v64 — jungle from the HERO PALM model (from v63). v63's invented plants
// looked like scattered flat planks. Now the jungle is populated with smaller,
// slimmer copies of the SAME hero palm (its clean trunk + structured fronds) at
// varied heights/depths/rotations + green shades, so it's coherent and good.
// Undergrowth is a few simple, clean voxel broad-leaf plants (neat rosettes, not
// a heap). Keeps the 3 depth layers + haze, the fast-then-slow growth, and the
// hero palm clearly in front. FocusWorld now takes the palm model as a template.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Voxel v63 — denser, layered focus jungle (from v62). The v62 jungle read as
// sparse twigs; this rebuilds FocusWorld for a real jungle COMPOSITION (voxel,
// not photoreal): tall slim voxel palms framing the focused palm, broad voxel
// leaves/fronds/bushes, lush undergrowth in front, and atmospheric DEPTH — back
// layers hazier/lighter (mist), front layers brighter — in 3 depth layers. Same
// fast-then-slow staggered growth; palm stays the hero in front. Reusable/themed.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Voxel v62 — focus view: a voxel JUNGLE grows around the palm (from v60, the
// working palm focus WITHOUT the v61 pedestal dressing, which was discarded).
// Tap the palm → it settles into focus, then a lush voxel jungle (small palms,
// ferns, broad-leaf plants, grasses, saplings) sprouts from the ground around
// it: a few pop fast for the wow, then growth slows and keeps filling in while
// you read the metaphor copy. On Back the jungle recedes with the scene.
// The growth world is components/v62/FocusWorld — generic + themed so the other
// 3 objects get their own world later. Panel copy is the longer Websites
// metaphor (focus.websites.tagline + .body), i18n via the existing switcher.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Voxel v60 — INTERACTIVITY B: click-to-focus, PALM only (copied from v59).
// Tap the palm (or its "Websites" label) → the island world recedes (everything
// but the palm fades out + the contact shadow melts), the palm glides to its
// showroom slot (LEFT on desktop / TOP on phone), scales up a touch and turns
// slowly like a product, and a "Websites" service panel slides in (RIGHT on
// desktop / BOTTOM on phone) with the i18n pitch + a "See our offers" CTA. A
// "Back" button / Esc / clicking the backdrop reverses everything back to the
// hero. Only the palm focuses in this step; the other 3 keep label + hover.
// The 3D side (palm focus rig + scene recede) lives in components/v60/SceneBuild;
// the island owns the focus flag and mirrors it to <html data-focus='websites'>,
// which this page uses to fade the hero text + reveal the panel. Panel copy is
// i18n (focus.* + services.websites.name), swapped by the existing switcher.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Voxel v59 — shape-hugging hitboxes (copied from v58). v58 tightened the boat
// with one explicit box, but the foreground palm + boat single boxes still
// projected over the background pitons/cruise ship (a box around a spread crown
// or a hull covers the empty gaps where the background peeks through). Replace
// the loose per-object AABB hit boxes with ONE invisible mesh per object whose
// geometry is the union of that object's actual voxel blocks (merged, slightly
// grown for comfy hover/tap). The hitbox now hugs the real shape, so each of the
// 4 objects raycasts to itself: palm->palm, boat->boat, pitons->pitons,
// ship->ship, with no foreground box blocking a background one. Badge style +
// anchors + everything else unchanged from v58.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Voxel v58 — badge style + hitbox raycast fixes (copied from v57). Two bugs:
//  (1) The AI Automation pill read grey/translucent because its background was
//      semi-transparent white (0.55) + blur: over the turquoise water the water
//      showed through, while the other three sit on the white sky. Make the pill
//      background fully opaque white so all four badges look identical.
//  (2) Hovering the pitons or the cruise ship highlighted the BOAT: the boat's
//      padded AABB hitbox was inflated back-and-left by its long propeller shaft
//      (world x to -3.85), and being closest to the camera it intercepted the
//      raycast meant for the objects behind it. A tight explicit boat hitbox
//      (HITBOX override, hull only) makes each of the 4 raycast to itself.
// Everything else is unchanged from v57.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Voxel v57 — AI Automation anchor onto the boat hull (copied from v56): the
// boat label's anchor/dot was floating at the boat pivot (y=0.55), projecting
// ~6% above the real hull so the connector landed on the island/water in front.
// Move ONLY the boat ANCHOR onto the deck amidships (world -0.52,0.09,2.21) so
// the dot/line sits clearly ON the longtail hull, and compensate its LABEL_OFFSET
// so the pill stays in the same clear lower-left water. The other 3 labels
// (Websites / Local SEO / Growth) are untouched. Framing/i18n as v56.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Voxel v56 — labels fully clear of busy content (copied from v55): the Websites
// (palm) pill was landing mid-fronds and AI Automation (boat) was over the
// water/island cubes. Push the palm label up into the clear sky above the crown
// and the boat label down-left into open water, both with longer connectors back
// to their on-object dot. Local SEO (pitons) + Growth (ship) kept as v55.
// Only LABEL_OFFSET (palm + boat) changes; anchors/framing/i18n as v55.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Voxel v55 — longer connectors + labels in negative space (copied from v54):
// the dot stays ON each object, but the pill is offset (LABEL_OFFSET) out into
// the empty sky/water, joined by a longer connector line — so labels no longer
// sit on the cubes. Palm/pitons/ship push up into the sky, the foreground boat
// pushes down into open water. Anchors/framing/i18n otherwise as v54.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Voxel v54 — fix the label ANCHORS (copied from v53): replace the AABB-derived
// anchors (which mis-placed AI Automation onto the pitons and cut Websites off
// the top) with explicit on-object 3D points; widen the PHONE framing (f 1.2→1.8,
// lookY 2.2→1.5) so all 4 objects + labels fit on a portrait screen. Desktop
// framing unchanged. Everything else as v53.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Voxel v53 — INTERACTIVITY A revised (copied from v52): replace the breathing
// glow with always-visible service LABEL pins (drei <Html>) on each of the 4
// objects (Websites / AI Automation / Local SEO / Growth). Discreet at rest,
// intensify + teal glow on hover (desktop) / tap (mobile). Label text is
// i18n-driven (EN passed as a prop from the JSON; the vanilla switcher swaps it
// via data-i18n + a pk-relabel event when the labels mount). Hitboxes/detection
// kept; tap still just identifies (no focus yet — part B).
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Voxel v52 — INTERACTIVITY part A (copied from v51): the 4 service objects
// (palm/boat/pitons/ship) get a teal clickable glow + generous invisible
// hitboxes + tap detection (logs/labels which object). NO focus transition yet
// (part B). Glow + raycasting live in components/v52 (SceneBuild); this page just
// lets pointer events reach the canvas (.hero-overlay pointer-events:none, real
// controls re-enabled). Hero intro / scene / i18n all unchanged.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Voxel v47 — HERO cinematic intro (copied from v46). Fixes the "everything
// stacked at once" overlap by playing a short staged intro on first visit, then
// settling into a clean, uncluttered resting state where nothing sits on the
// palm/boat/pitons.
//
// Intro (first visit only): big centred HEADLINE → big SUBTITLE → then the chip
// lands AND the scene builds. ~1.3s/step, skippable (scroll/tap/key), first-visit
// flag in localStorage. Return visits + reduced-motion land on the rest state
// instantly. The scene build is GATED via window.__pkHero (held invisible until
// the chip step) — the React island reads/subscribes to it (see PalmTreeHero/
// SceneBuild `gate`).
//
// Rest state: scene + discreet chip + COMPACT headline (top band, clear of the
// palm) + CTA (thumb zone) + EN/FR/TH switcher. The long subtitle is dropped at
// rest (it had its moment in the intro). All copy stays in src/i18n/*.json.
import '../styles/global.css';
import PalmTreeHero from '../components/v64/PalmTreeHero.tsx';
import en from '../i18n/v64/en.json';
import fr from '../i18n/v64/fr.json';
import th from '../i18n/v64/th.json';

const i18n = { en, fr, th };
const t = en; // server-render the EN copy for instant first paint + SEO

type Svc = { name: string; desc: string };
const langs = ['en', 'fr', 'th'] as const;
const svcKeys = ['websites', 'ai', 'seo', 'growth'] as const;
const services = t.services as Record<string, Svc>;
const svc = svcKeys.map((key, i) => ({ key, num: String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0'), ...services[key] }));
// EN service names (from the JSON, not hardcoded) → initial 3D label text; the
// vanilla switcher swaps them by language on mount (pk-relabel) + on click.
const heroLabels = {
  palm: services.websites.name, boat: services.ai.name, piton: services.seo.name, ship: services.growth.name,
};
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, viewport-fit=cover" />
    <title>Palmkit Studio. Faster. Further. For less.</title>
    <meta name="description" content="A web & AI studio from Phuket. Faster, further, for less. Websites, growth & automation." />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:opsz,wght@9..144,500;9..144,600&family=Hanken+Grotesk:wght@400;500;600&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <!-- Pre-paint: decide intro vs rest (no FOUC) + seed the scene-build gate +
         force a top-of-page start (no restored scroll / no #services anchor jump). -->
    <script is:inline>
      (function () {
        try { if ('scrollRestoration' in history) history.scrollRestoration = 'manual'; } catch (e) {}
        // a fresh load should always start at the top of the hero, never at #services
        if (location.hash) { try { history.replaceState(null, '', location.pathname + location.search); } catch (e) {} }
        var reduce = false;
        try { reduce = matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches; } catch (e) {}
        var play = !reduce; // play the intro on EVERY load (no first-visit flag)
        window.__pkHero = { mode: play ? 'hold' : 'instant', notify: null };
        document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-hero', play ? 'intro-1' : 'rest');
      })();
    </script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <!-- ===================== HERO ===================== -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-dawn" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="hero-canvas"><PalmTreeHero client:only="react" labels={heroLabels} /></div>
      <div class="hero-scrim" aria-hidden="true"></div>

      <!-- INTRO: big centred text, staged (plays every load). The subtitle carries
           <strong> emphasis, so it uses set:html / data-i18n-html (switcher swaps
           innerHTML for those). The 3rd step is a centred "From Phuket" that blooms
           in WITH the scene then cross-fades out as the build completes. -->
      <div class="intro" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="intro-line intro-headline" data-i18n="headline">{t.headline}</div>
        <div class="intro-line intro-subtitle" data-i18n-html="subtitle" set:html={t.subtitle}></div>
        <div class="intro-line intro-chip" data-i18n="chip">{t.chip}</div>
      </div>

      <!-- REST: clean overlay, text in top/bottom bands (no overlap with the palm) -->
      <div class="hero-overlay">
        <header class="hero-top">
          <span class="chip" data-i18n="chip">{t.chip}</span>
          <nav class="lang" aria-label="Language">
            {
              langs.map((code) => (
                <button type="button" class="lang-btn" data-lang-btn={code} aria-pressed={code === 'en' ? 'true' : 'false'}>
                  {i18n[code].langName}
                </button>
              ))
            }
          </nav>
        </header>

        <h1 class="headline-compact" data-i18n="headline">{t.headline}</h1>

        <div class="hero-foot">
          <button type="button" class="cta" data-cta data-i18n="cta">{t.cta}</button>
          <button type="button" class="scroll-cue" data-cta aria-label={t.scrollCue}>
            <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FOCUS (INTERACTIVITY B): click-catching backdrop + the "Websites"
           service panel. Hidden until the island sets <html data-focus='websites'>
           (tap the palm / its label). Copy is i18n via data-i18n. -->
      <div class="focus-backdrop" data-focus-close aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <aside class="focus-panel" role="dialog" aria-modal="false" aria-labelledby="focus-title">
        <button type="button" class="focus-back" data-focus-close>
          <span class="focus-back-arrow" aria-hidden="true">←</span>
          <span data-i18n="focus.back">{t.focus.back}</span>
        </button>
        <p class="focus-eyebrow" data-i18n="chip">{t.chip}</p>
        <h2 class="focus-title" id="focus-title" data-i18n="services.websites.name">{t.services.websites.name}</h2>
        <p class="focus-tagline" data-i18n="focus.websites.tagline">{t.focus.websites.tagline}</p>
        <p class="focus-body" data-i18n="focus.websites.body">{t.focus.websites.body}</p>
        <button type="button" class="focus-cta" data-cta data-focus-close data-i18n="cta">{t.cta}</button>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <!-- ===================== SERVICES ===================== -->
    <section id="services" class="services">
      <div class="services-inner">
        <h2 class="services-title" data-i18n="servicesTitle">{t.servicesTitle}</h2>
        <ul class="cards">
          {
            svc.map((s) => (
              <li class="card">
                <span class="card-num">{s.num}</span>
                <h3 class="card-name" data-i18n={`services.${s.key}.name`}>{s.name}</h3>
                <p class="card-desc" data-i18n={`services.${s.key}.desc`}>{s.desc}</p>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <a href="/versions" class="versions-link">← All versions</a>

    <script define:vars={{ i18n }}>
      const html = document.documentElement;

      // ---- always start at the TOP of the hero on a fresh load ----------------
      window.scrollTo(0, 0);
      window.addEventListener('load', function () { window.scrollTo(0, 0); });

      // ---- i18n switcher: swap [data-i18n] text from the inlined dicts --------
      const resolve = (dict, path) => path.split('.').reduce((o, k) => (o == null ? o : o[k]), dict);
      let activeLang = 'en';
      function applyLang(lang) {
        activeLang = lang;
        const dict = i18n[lang] || i18n.en;
        document.querySelectorAll('[data-i18n]').forEach((el) => {
          const v = resolve(dict, el.getAttribute('data-i18n'));
          if (typeof v === 'string') el.textContent = v;
        });
        // HTML-bearing strings (e.g. the subtitle's <strong> emphasis): innerHTML.
        document.querySelectorAll('[data-i18n-html]').forEach((el) => {
          const v = resolve(dict, el.getAttribute('data-i18n-html'));
          if (typeof v === 'string') el.innerHTML = v;
        });
        html.setAttribute('lang', lang);
        document.querySelectorAll('[data-lang-btn]').forEach((b) => {
          b.setAttribute('aria-pressed', String(b.getAttribute('data-lang-btn') === lang));
        });
        try { localStorage.setItem('pk-lang', lang); } catch (e) {}
      }
      let savedLang = null;
      try { savedLang = localStorage.getItem('pk-lang'); } catch (e) {}
      applyLang(savedLang && i18n[savedLang] ? savedLang : 'en');
      document.querySelectorAll('[data-lang-btn]').forEach((b) => {
        b.addEventListener('click', () => applyLang(b.getAttribute('data-lang-btn')));
      });
      // The 3D service labels (drei <Html>) mount after this initial applyLang —
      // re-apply the active language to those late [data-i18n] nodes.
      window.addEventListener('pk-relabel', () => applyLang(activeLang));

      // ---- intro orchestrator ------------------------------------------------
      function release(mode) {
        if (!window.__pkHero) window.__pkHero = { mode };
        window.__pkHero.mode = mode;
        if (window.__pkHero.notify) window.__pkHero.notify(mode); // wake the scene island
      }

      // Plays on EVERY load (the pre-paint script set intro-1 unless reduced-motion).
      if (html.getAttribute('data-hero') === 'intro-1') {
        const timers = [];
        let done = false;
        // NB: no 'scroll' here — the programmatic scroll-to-top must not count as a skip.
        const skipEvents = ['wheel', 'touchstart', 'pointerdown', 'keydown'];
        function cleanup() { skipEvents.forEach((e) => window.removeEventListener(e, onSkip)); }
        function finish(instant) {
          if (done) return; done = true;
          timers.forEach(clearTimeout);
          cleanup();
          html.setAttribute('data-hero', 'rest');
          release(instant ? 'instant' : 'build');
        }
        function onSkip() { finish(true); } // skip → jump straight to the built rest state
        // Pacing: headline ~1s hold (short line) → subtitle ~3.3s hold (2
        // sentences) → STEP 3: a centred "From Phuket" blooms in AND the scene is
        // released to build at the same moment; the centred chip then cross-fades
        // out over the build (CSS chipBloom, ~3.2s), ending on the scene alone;
        // finally the resting layout settles in.
        timers.push(setTimeout(() => { if (!done) html.setAttribute('data-hero', 'intro-2'); }, 1900));
        timers.push(setTimeout(() => {
          if (done) return;
          html.setAttribute('data-hero', 'intro-3'); // centred "From Phuket"
          release('build'); // scene starts building behind it, same moment
        }, 6200));
        timers.push(setTimeout(() => finish(false), 9400)); // ~build duration later → rest layout
        skipEvents.forEach((e) => window.addEventListener(e, onSkip, { passive: true, once: true }));
      }

      // ---- CTA + scroll cue: smooth-scroll to #services ----------------------
      const reduceMotion = matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;
      const target = document.getElementById('services');
      document.querySelectorAll('[data-cta]').forEach((el) => {
        el.addEventListener('click', () => target?.scrollIntoView({ behavior: reduceMotion ? 'auto' : 'smooth', block: 'start' }));
      });

      // ---- v60: close the service focus (Back / backdrop / CTA) --------------
      // The island owns the focus flag (it opens on palm tap + drives the 3D); the
      // page just asks it to CLOSE via a pk-focus-set event. Esc is handled inside
      // the island. Opening is the palm tap, not a DOM control.
      document.querySelectorAll('[data-focus-close]').forEach((el) => {
        el.addEventListener('click', () => window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('pk-focus-set', { detail: { on: false } })));
      });
    </script>

    <style is:global>
      :root {
        --ink: #1c2b26;
        --coral: #ff6b4a;
        --teal: #15a8ae;
        --font-display: 'Fraunces', Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
        --font-body: 'Hanken Grotesk', system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
        --ease: cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1); /* calm, premium ease-out */
      }
      html, body { margin: 0; padding: 0; background: #fbfcfd; color: var(--ink); font-family: var(--font-body); }
      * { box-sizing: border-box; }

      /* ---- HERO shell ---- */
      .hero { position: relative; width: 100%; height: 100vh; height: 100svh; overflow: hidden; }
      .hero-dawn, .hero-canvas, .hero-scrim, .hero-overlay, .intro { position: absolute; inset: 0; }
      .hero-dawn {
        z-index: 0;
        background:
          radial-gradient(60% 50% at 39% 27%, #ffdca6 0%, rgba(255, 220, 166, 0) 60%),
          linear-gradient(180deg, #fbfcfd 0%, #fbfcfd 45%, #ffe6c2 100%);
      }
      .hero-canvas { z-index: 1; }
      .hero-canvas > * { width: 100%; height: 100%; }
      /* Legibility scrim removed (v51): the text reads fine on the pale scene via
         its own text-shadow / chip pill, and the veil looked like a whitish patch. */
      .hero-scrim { z-index: 2; pointer-events: none; background: none; }

      /* ---- INTRO (big centred, staged, premium) ---- */
      .intro {
        z-index: 4; display: grid; place-items: center; text-align: center; padding: 1.75rem;
        pointer-events: none;
        /* a calm, controlled veil so the text is the clear focus over the held scene */
        background: radial-gradient(70% 50% at 50% 47%, rgba(255, 253, 248, 0.62) 0%, rgba(255, 253, 248, 0.18) 45%, rgba(255, 253, 248, 0) 78%);
        transition: opacity 0.8s var(--ease);
      }
      /* soft rise + fade + blur entrance; drifts gently up + blurs out on exit */
      .intro-line {
        position: absolute; margin: 0; max-width: 20rem;
        opacity: 0; transform: translateY(22px); filter: blur(7px);
        transition: opacity 0.95s var(--ease), transform 1.05s var(--ease), filter 0.95s var(--ease);
        text-shadow: 0 1px 16px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
      }
      .intro-headline {
        font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 11vw, 4.8rem);
        line-height: 1.04; letter-spacing: -0.015em; color: var(--ink);
      }
      .intro-subtitle {
        font-family: var(--font-body); font-weight: 400; font-size: clamp(1.08rem, 4.5vw, 1.5rem);
        line-height: 1.55; letter-spacing: 0.002em; color: #2c3e36; max-width: 22rem;
      }
      .intro-subtitle strong { font-weight: 600; color: var(--ink); } /* emphasise only the catchy phrases */
      /* centred "From Phuket" — a brand stamp during the scene bloom */
      .intro-chip {
        font-family: var(--font-body); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.16em;
        font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 4vw, 1.35rem); color: var(--ink);
        display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.6rem;
      }
      .intro-chip::before { content: ''; width: 0.5rem; height: 0.5rem; border-radius: 999px; background: var(--coral); }
      @media (min-width: 768px) {
        .intro-headline { max-width: 46rem; }
        .intro-subtitle { max-width: 40rem; }
      }

      /* enter (current step) */
      html[data-hero='intro-1'] .intro-headline,
      html[data-hero='intro-2'] .intro-subtitle { opacity: 1; transform: none; filter: blur(0); }
      /* exit (past steps): drift up + blur out, never a flat cut */
      html[data-hero='intro-2'] .intro-headline,
      html[data-hero='intro-3'] .intro-headline,
      html[data-hero='rest'] .intro-headline,
      html[data-hero='intro-3'] .intro-subtitle,
      html[data-hero='rest'] .intro-subtitle { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-16px); filter: blur(6px); }
      /* STEP 3: centred "From Phuket" blooms in WITH the scene, holds, then
         cross-fades out over the build (~3.2s) — ends on the scene alone. */
      @keyframes chipBloom {
        0%   { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(14px); filter: blur(6px); }
        20%  { opacity: 1; transform: none; filter: blur(0); }
        55%  { opacity: 1; transform: none; filter: blur(0); }
        100% { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-12px); filter: blur(5px); }
      }
      html[data-hero='intro-3'] .intro-chip { animation: chipBloom 3.2s var(--ease) forwards; }
      html[data-hero='rest'] .intro { opacity: 0; }

      /* ---- REST overlay ---- */
      .hero-overlay {
        z-index: 3; display: flex; flex-direction: column;
        padding: max(1.1rem, env(safe-area-inset-top)) 1.25rem max(1.4rem, env(safe-area-inset-bottom));
        /* v52: let taps fall through to the 3D objects; re-enable on real controls */
        pointer-events: none;
      }
      .lang, .cta, .scroll-cue { pointer-events: auto; }
      /* Each piece animates individually so the CHIP arrives WITH the scene bloom,
         then the rest (headline / CTA / switcher) settles in just after. */
      .chip, .lang, .headline-compact, .hero-foot {
        opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px);
        transition: opacity 0.9s var(--ease), transform 0.9s var(--ease);
      }
      /* CHIP — in sync with the scene reveal (same moment) */
      html[data-hero='rest'] .chip { opacity: 1; transform: none; transition-delay: 0.1s; }
      /* the rest of the resting UI — settles in shortly after */
      html[data-hero='rest'] .lang,
      html[data-hero='rest'] .headline-compact,
      html[data-hero='rest'] .hero-foot { opacity: 1; transform: none; transition-delay: 0.85s; }

      .hero-top { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: space-between; gap: 1rem; }
      .chip {
        display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.45rem;
        font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink);
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.62); backdrop-filter: blur(6px);
        border: 1px solid rgba(21, 168, 174, 0.4); padding: 0.32rem 0.7rem; border-radius: 999px;
      }
      .chip::before { content: ''; width: 0.42rem; height: 0.42rem; border-radius: 999px; background: var(--coral); }

      .lang { display: inline-flex; gap: 0.15rem; background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55); backdrop-filter: blur(6px); border: 1px solid rgba(28, 43, 38, 0.12); border-radius: 999px; padding: 0.15rem; }
      .lang-btn { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 600; color: #5b6b64; background: transparent; border: 0; border-radius: 999px; padding: 0.28rem 0.55rem; cursor: pointer; transition: background 0.18s, color 0.18s; }
      .lang-btn[aria-pressed='true'] { background: var(--ink); color: #fff; }

      .headline-compact {
        font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; margin: 0.8rem 0 0; max-width: 17rem;
        font-size: clamp(1.45rem, 6.5vw, 2.1rem); line-height: 1.05; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--ink);
        text-shadow: 0 1px 8px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
      }

      .hero-foot { margin-top: auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 0.85rem; }
      .cta {
        font-family: var(--font-body); font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.02rem; color: var(--ink);
        background: var(--coral); border: 0; border-radius: 999px; padding: 0.85rem 1.6rem; cursor: pointer;
        box-shadow: 0 10px 24px -10px rgba(255, 107, 74, 0.7); transition: transform 0.18s, box-shadow 0.18s;
      }
      .cta:hover { transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 16px 30px -12px rgba(255, 107, 74, 0.8); }
      .cta:active { transform: translateY(0); }
      .scroll-cue { align-self: center; width: 2.2rem; height: 2.2rem; background: transparent; border: 0; cursor: pointer; display: grid; place-items: center; }
      .chev { width: 0.8rem; height: 0.8rem; border-right: 2px solid #5b6b64; border-bottom: 2px solid #5b6b64; transform: rotate(45deg); animation: cue 1.8s ease-in-out infinite; }
      @keyframes cue { 0%, 100% { transform: rotate(45deg) translate(0, 0); opacity: 0.5; } 50% { transform: rotate(45deg) translate(2px, 2px); opacity: 1; } }

      @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
        .intro-line, .intro, .hero-overlay,
        .chip, .lang, .headline-compact, .hero-foot { transition: none; }
        .chev, .intro-chip { animation: none; }
      }

      /* ---- DESKTOP: text in the upper-left band, scene full-bleed ---- */
      @media (min-width: 768px) {
        .hero-overlay { padding: 2rem 3rem; }
        .headline-compact { margin-top: 12vh; font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 3vw, 2.8rem); max-width: 22rem; }
        .hero-foot { margin-top: 1.8rem; flex-direction: row; align-items: center; gap: 1.4rem; }
        .scroll-cue { position: absolute; left: 50%; bottom: 1.5rem; transform: translateX(-50%); align-self: auto; }
        /* desktop scrim also removed (v51) — no left/diagonal white patch */
      }

      /* ---- SERVICES ---- */
      .services { background: #fbfcfd; padding: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 6rem) 1.25rem clamp(4rem, 10vw, 7rem); }
      .services-inner { max-width: 64rem; margin: 0 auto; }
      .services-title { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 5vw, 2.4rem); margin: 0 0 1.8rem; color: var(--ink); }
      .cards { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.9rem; }
      @media (min-width: 560px) { .cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }
      @media (min-width: 960px) { .cards { grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); } }
      .card { position: relative; background: #fff; border: 1px solid rgba(28, 43, 38, 0.1); border-radius: 1rem; padding: 1.3rem 1.2rem 1.4rem; transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s, border-color 0.2s; }
      .card:hover { transform: translateY(-3px); box-shadow: 0 18px 36px -22px rgba(28, 43, 38, 0.5); border-color: rgba(21, 168, 174, 0.5); }
      .card-num { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--teal); }
      .card-name { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.2rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.35rem; color: var(--ink); }
      .card-desc { margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.45; color: #5b6b64; }

      /* ---- 3D service label pins (drei <Html> content) ---- */
      /* (0,0) of the pin = the object anchor: the dot sits ON the object, a longer
         connector runs out to the pill which floats in clear space (var --dx/--dy).
         Hidden during the intro; fade in with the final scene. */
      .svc-pin {
        position: relative; width: 0; height: 0; pointer-events: none; user-select: none;
        opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0.7s var(--ease) 0.2s;
      }
      html[data-hero='rest'] .svc-pin { opacity: 1; }
      html[data-hero='rest'] .svc-pill { pointer-events: auto; }
      .svc-anchor-dot {
        position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0; width: 7px; height: 7px; margin: -3.5px; border-radius: 999px;
        background: #5fe3d6; box-shadow: 0 0 7px rgba(95, 227, 214, 0.9);
      }
      .svc-connector {
        position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0; height: 1.5px; width: var(--len); transform-origin: 0 50%;
        transform: rotate(var(--ang)); background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(95, 227, 214, 0.85), rgba(95, 227, 214, 0.3));
      }
      .svc-pill {
        position: absolute; left: var(--dx); top: var(--dy); transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
        pointer-events: none; cursor: pointer; white-space: nowrap;
        font: 600 0.72rem/1 var(--font-body); letter-spacing: 0.01em; color: var(--ink);
        background: #ffffff;
        border: 1px solid rgba(21, 168, 174, 0.4); border-radius: 999px; padding: 0.3rem 0.62rem;
        box-shadow: 0 3px 10px -5px rgba(28, 43, 38, 0.4);
        opacity: 0.82; transition: opacity 0.2s var(--ease), transform 0.2s var(--ease), border-color 0.2s, background 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
      }
      .svc-pin.is-active .svc-pill { opacity: 1; transform: translate(-50%, -50%) scale(1.08); border-color: #5fe3d6; background: #ffffff; box-shadow: 0 5px 16px -5px rgba(95, 227, 214, 0.7); }
      .svc-pin.is-active .svc-anchor-dot { box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(95, 227, 214, 1); }
      .svc-pin.is-active .svc-connector { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #5fe3d6, rgba(95, 227, 214, 0.5)); height: 2px; }
      @media (min-width: 768px) { .svc-pill { font-size: 0.78rem; } }
      /* v60: hide all 3D labels while a service is in focus (the panel carries the
         title); they fade via the .svc-pin opacity transition. */
      .svc-pin.is-hidden { opacity: 0 !important; pointer-events: none !important; }

      .versions-link { position: fixed; bottom: 0.6rem; right: 0.6rem; z-index: 50; font-size: 0.72rem; color: #5b6b64; text-decoration: none; background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8); backdrop-filter: blur(4px); border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08); border-radius: 0.5rem; padding: 0.3rem 0.55rem; }

      /* ============================ v60 FOCUS ============================ */
      /* When the island sets <html data-focus='websites'>: fade the hero text,
         show the backdrop + the "Websites" panel. Reverse smoothly on Back. */
      .hero-overlay { transition: opacity 0.55s var(--ease); }
      html[data-focus='websites'] .hero-overlay { opacity: 0; pointer-events: none; }
      html[data-focus='websites'] .versions-link { opacity: 0; pointer-events: none; transition: opacity 0.4s var(--ease); }

      .focus-backdrop {
        position: absolute; inset: 0; z-index: 5; opacity: 0; pointer-events: none;
        background: transparent; transition: opacity 0.55s var(--ease);
      }
      html[data-focus='websites'] .focus-backdrop { opacity: 1; pointer-events: auto; }

      .focus-panel {
        position: absolute; z-index: 6; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start;
        gap: 0.6rem; pointer-events: none; opacity: 0;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95); -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(10px); backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
        transition: opacity 0.6s var(--ease), transform 0.6s var(--ease);
        /* MOBILE (default): a bottom sheet — thumb-friendly, readable on narrow screens.
           Capped + scrollable so the longer metaphor copy never overflows a phone. */
        left: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0; max-height: 64svh; overflow-y: auto;
        padding: 1.3rem 1.4rem max(1.5rem, env(safe-area-inset-bottom));
        border-radius: 1.25rem 1.25rem 0 0;
        box-shadow: 0 -16px 40px -20px rgba(28, 43, 38, 0.45);
        border-top: 1px solid rgba(28, 43, 38, 0.08);
        transform: translateY(28px);
      }
      html[data-focus='websites'] .focus-panel { opacity: 1; pointer-events: auto; transform: none; }

      .focus-back {
        display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem; align-self: flex-start;
        font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.82rem; font-weight: 600; color: #5b6b64;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); border: 1px solid rgba(28, 43, 38, 0.14);
        border-radius: 999px; padding: 0.42rem 0.85rem; cursor: pointer;
        transition: background 0.18s, color 0.18s, border-color 0.18s;
      }
      .focus-back:hover { color: var(--ink); border-color: rgba(21, 168, 174, 0.5); }
      .focus-back-arrow { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1; }
      .focus-eyebrow {
        margin: 0.2rem 0 0; font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.14em;
        text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--teal);
      }
      .focus-title {
        margin: 0; font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--ink);
        font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 8vw, 2.4rem); line-height: 1.05;
      }
      .focus-tagline {
        margin: 0.1rem 0 0; max-width: 32rem; font-family: var(--font-display); font-style: italic;
        font-weight: 500; font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 4.6vw, 1.3rem); line-height: 1.3; color: var(--teal);
      }
      .focus-body {
        margin: 0; max-width: 32rem; color: #344a40; font-size: 0.98rem; line-height: 1.58;
      }
      .focus-cta {
        margin-top: 0.35rem; font-family: var(--font-body); font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.02rem; color: #fff;
        background: var(--coral); border: 0; border-radius: 999px; padding: 0.85rem 1.7rem; cursor: pointer;
        box-shadow: 0 10px 24px -10px rgba(255, 107, 74, 0.7); transition: transform 0.18s, box-shadow 0.18s;
      }
      .focus-cta:hover { transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 16px 30px -12px rgba(255, 107, 74, 0.85); }
      .focus-cta:active { transform: translateY(0); }

      /* DESKTOP: a right-hand column, vertically centred; palm glides to the left. */
      @media (min-width: 768px) {
        .focus-panel {
          left: auto; top: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0; justify-content: center;
          width: min(42vw, 30rem); gap: 1rem;
          /* full-height clean column — drop the mobile bottom-sheet cap/scroll */
          max-height: none; overflow: visible;
          padding: 2rem clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);
          border-radius: 0; border-top: 0; border-left: 1px solid rgba(28, 43, 38, 0.08);
          box-shadow: -24px 0 60px -30px rgba(28, 43, 38, 0.4);
          transform: translateX(32px);
        }
        html[data-focus='websites'] .focus-panel { transform: none; }
        .focus-title { font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 3vw, 3rem); }
        .focus-tagline { font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 1.6vw, 1.5rem); }
        .focus-body { font-size: 1.05rem; }
        .focus-panel { gap: 0.7rem; }
      }

      @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
        .hero-overlay, .focus-backdrop, .focus-panel, .versions-link { transition: none; }
      }
    </style>
  </body>
</html>
